# Monday Board Structure

## Patterns to Flag

- Board definitions or migrations that create roughly 30 or more columns on a single board without strong justification
- Boards modeled with a single group while item count or workflow implies multiple phases (everything in "Group Title" only)
- Mixed column naming conventions on the same board (e.g., `camelCase` and `snake_case` column titles or IDs in config)
- Status columns with large sets of labels where most are unused or duplicate semantics
- Project or timeline-oriented boards missing timeline and/or date columns when scheduling is clearly required

## What to Do

- Split wide boards into linked boards, views, or connected items; archive unused columns
- Use multiple groups for stages, teams, or batches; align group names with the actual workflow
- Pick one naming convention for titles and stable identifiers in JSON/config and apply it consistently
- Trim status labels to active values; document mapping in team docs
- Add timeline or date columns for boards that track deadlines, sprints, or Gantt-style work

## Exceptions

- Import/migration JSON that is intermediate and will be normalized in a follow-up step
- Generated snapshots from the API for read-only reporting (not authoring new structure)
- Template JSON in documentation marked as illustrative only
